comments.author: SincerelySaida

comments.text:
+SincerelySaida Wallahi is an Arabic word, not Swahili (although the 
language Swahili is heavily influenced by Arabic). Islam is the biggest 
religion in Africa, both in sub-Sahara and North Africa, and therefore 
Arabic words that have to do with religion are common in many parts of 
Africa such as wallahi, astagfurallah, and other words.

+Dimitri Abdul Nour While the word is Arabic, all Muslims use it or are 
familiar with it. The majority of Muslims in the world are non-Arab, 
contrary to popular belief and seeing as how Somalis popularized the word 
in places with a noticeably large Somali community (ie. Toronto, London in 
England, Minneapolis in MN, etc). Seeing as how she lived in Toronto, it's 
very likely she picked it up from Somalis or, in this case, her boyfriend 
who is Tanzanian.
